======================================================================
PART 2: WHAT IS n + C(n,3)?
======================================================================
  n + C(n,3) = C(n,1) + C(n,3)
  This is the sum of the FIRST TWO odd binomial coefficients!

  Full odd sum: C(n,1) + C(n,3) + C(n,5) + ... = 2^(n-1)
  Our sequence = the PARTIAL sum C(n,1) + C(n,3)

  Compare with:
  C(n,0) + C(n,2) + C(n,4) + ... = 2^(n-1) (even sum)

  So a(n)/2^(n-1) -> 0 as n -> infinity (only 2 of ~n/2 terms)

