PART 3: STRANDS OF a(n) = C(n,1) + C(n,3)
======================================================================

  Even-index strand: a(0), a(2), a(4), a(6), ...
    a( 0) =      0
    a( 2) =      2
    a( 4) =      8
    a( 6) =     26
    a( 8) =     64
    a(10) =    130
    a(12) =    232
    a(14) =    378

  Odd-index strand: a(1), a(3), a(5), a(7), ...
    a( 1) =      1
    a( 3) =      4
    a( 5) =     15
    a( 7) =     42
    a( 9) =     93
    a(11) =    176
    a(13) =    299
    a(15) =    470

  SYMMETRY: a(n) + a(-n) = -n^2
  Verification:
    a(1) + a(-1) = 1 + -2 = -1, -n^2 = -1, match = True
    a(2) + a(-2) = 2 + -6 = -4, -n^2 = -4, match = True
    a(3) + a(-3) = 4 + -13 = -9, -n^2 = -9, match = True
    a(4) + a(-4) = 8 + -24 = -16, -n^2 = -16, match = True
    a(5) + a(-5) = 15 + -40 = -25, -n^2 = -25, match = True
    a(6) + a(-6) = 26 + -62 = -36, -n^2 = -36, match = True

  So: a(n) = (-n^2 - a(-n))/1... or better:
  a(n) - a(-n) = 2n + n(n-1)(n-2)/6 + n(n+1)(n+2)/6
  = 2n + n[(n-1)(n-2) + (n+1)(n+2)]/6
  = 2n + n[2n^2 + 4]/6
  = 2n + n(n^2+2)/3

